headline: How New Missile and Air Defense Test Milestones At Northrop Grumman (NOC) Have Changed Its Investment Story
summary: Northrop Grumman recently completed a successful separation test of its Stand-In Attack Weapon from a U.S. Air Force F-16, and the U.S. Army’s Integrated Battle Command System intercepted cruise missiles in a realistic test, underscoring progress across advanced weapons and command systems. These test milestones highlight Northrop Grumman’s growing role in integrating next-generation missiles and air‑and‑missile defense networks that can be scaled for both U.S. and allied customers.
